## Git-Based Deployment

The server runs from a git clone of `https://github.com/JoseMoura97/ib_bot.git` on branch `portfolios-builder-allocations-ui`.

**Deploy workflow (local):**
1. Commit and push changes locally: `git push origin portfolios-builder-allocations-ui`
2. Run deploy on server via SSH:
```bash
ssh root@213.159.68.39 "cd /home/ibbot/ib_bot && GIT_TERMINAL_PROMPT=0 git pull origin portfolios-builder-allocations-ui && docker compose -f docker-compose.yml -f docker-compose.prod.yml up -d --build"
```

Or use the deploy script on the server:
```bash
ssh root@213.159.68.39 "/home/ibbot/deploy.sh"
```

**Important:** Always commit and push ALL files the server needs (including migrations) before deploying. The server only gets what's in git. `.env` and `.cache` are gitignored and persist independently on the server.

## Common Operations

```bash
# Check status
docker compose ps

# View logs
docker compose logs -f [service]

# Restart after config change
docker compose -f docker-compose.yml -f docker-compose.prod.yml up -d

# Rebuild after code change
docker compose -f docker-compose.yml -f docker-compose.prod.yml up -d --build

# Database access
docker compose exec db psql -U ibbot -d ibbot

# Emergency stop trading
echo "TRADING_HALT=true" >> .env && docker compose restart api worker
```

